ce:section.ce:para:
The CDs and CPBA-CDs were characterized by TEM (Fig. 2
                        ). It can be seen from the typical TEM images that the as-prepared CDs are nearly uniform in size (about 3.75nm, Fig. 2C) and the size of CPBA-CDs is 7.5nm (Fig. 2D), and clear crystalline structure of CPBA-CDs was also displayed in HR-TEM image (inset: Fig. 2B). However, the CPBA functionalized CDs nanoparticles showed no obvious morphology change after the surface functionalization. Furthermore, the FT-IR spectra of the CDs and CPBA-CDs are shown in Fig. 3
                         to further characterize the formation of CPBA-CDs. As illustrated in Fig. 3, the obtained CDs and CPBA-CDs exhibit characteristic absorption bands of OH and NH stretching vibrations of amine groups at 3400cm−1, the absorption band at about 3140cm−1 is assigned to the unsaturated CH stretching and the peak near 1560cm−1 was attributed to the bending stretching of NH [30,31]. Besides, 1380cm−1 is assigned to the stretching of CN and 1680cm−1 was the vibration absorption peak of CO [32,33]. The peaks at for 2750 and 840cm−1 are CN and phenyl. The FT-IR spectra of the CPBA-CDs also exhibited absorption bands at 1360, 1193, 1116 and 1032cm−1, which could be attributed to BO stretching vibration, BOH bending vibration, CB stretching mode and BOH deformation vibration, respectively [34,35]. These results further demonstrated that the CDs were successfully functionalized by CPBA.
